name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Though it may look like it's just a bunch of eggs, it's a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Shroomish
flavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

name: Breloom
flavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if this Pokémon used Spore Ball during your last turn.

name: Tropius
flavorText: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.
Ability1Text: All of your Pokémon that have Grass Energy attached can't be Confused, and if they are already Confused, they recover from that Special Condition.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

name: Grotle
flavorText: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Torterra
flavorText: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Evolution Pokémon in play.

name: Burmy
flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

name: Wormadam
flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Mothim
flavorText: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon evolved from Burmy during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Cherubi
flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

name: Shaymin V
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Shaymin VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may heal 120 damage from each of your Benched Grass Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Karrablast
flavorText: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

name: Zarude V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Charizard V
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Charizard VSTAR
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Magmar
flavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Magmortar
flavorText: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack2Text: If Electivire is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Moltres
flavorText: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 70 more damage. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Entei V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Torkoal
flavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Chimchar
flavorText: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Monferno
flavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Infernape
flavorText: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.
Attack1Text: Reveal the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 80 damage for each Energy card you find there. Then, discard those Energy cards and shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Simisear V
Attack1Text: You may attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your hand to your Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Kingler V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 5 Water Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Kingler VMAX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 5 Water Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Staryu
flavorText: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you'll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Lapras
flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Corphish
flavorText: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

name: Crawdaunt
flavorText: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It can only survive in cold areas. It bounces happily around, even in environments as cold as -150 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Piplup
flavorText: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Prinplup
flavorText: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

name: Empoleon
flavorText: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your discard pile and you have no cards in your hand, you may put this Pokémon onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Buizel
flavorText: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Floatzel
flavorText: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.
Attack1Text: Put up to 2 Item cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Lumineon V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.

name: Manaphy
flavorText: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Cubchoo
flavorText: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn't like.

name: Beartic
flavorText: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

name: Eiscue
flavorText: The hair on its head connects to the surface of its brain. When this Pokémon has something on its mind, its hair chills the air around it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Fusion Strike Energy attached to all of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Raichu V
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: You may discard any amount of Lightning Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Electivire
flavorText: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.
Attack1Text: If any of your Benched Magmortar have any damage counters on them, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Raikou V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Shinx
flavorText: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

name: Luxio
flavorText: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokémon can receive some of the other Luxio's electricity and power up its own electric blasts.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Luxray
flavorText: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Pachirisu
flavorText: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. Choose a number of your Pokémon in play up to the number of heads. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Starmie
flavorText: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Granbull V
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Claydol
flavorText: This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.
Attack2Text: If you and your opponent have the same number of Benched Pokémon, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Duskull
flavorText: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it's said.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Special Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

name: Chimecho
flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Special Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Whimsicott V
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Whimsicott VSTAR
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Pokémon Tool or Special Energy cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. Attach a number of basic Energy cards up to the number of heads from your discard pile to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Since Dedenne can't generate as much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, this attack does 60 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Mimikyu V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may prevent all damage done to this Mimikyu V by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon until the end of your opponent's next turn.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Mimikyu VMAX
Attack1Text: Put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like. If you played Acerola's Premonition from your hand during this turn, place 13 damage counters instead.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Milcery
flavorText: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Alcremie
flavorText: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your turn does not end when you use Café Master.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each type of basic Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Hitmontop
flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Nosepass
flavorText: It hunts without twitching a muscle by pulling in its prey with powerful magnetism. But sometimes it pulls natural enemies in close.

name: Trapinch
flavorText: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Vibrava
flavorText: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.

name: Flygon
flavorText: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

name: Wormadam
flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

name: Lucario
flavorText: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on this Pokémon. If you do, search your deck for a Fighting Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Discard all Fighting Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 60 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Throh
flavorText: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh's belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer's sweat.

name: Sawk
flavorText: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it's best to quietly pass by.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Golett
flavorText: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

name: Golurk
flavorText: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each card in your hand.

name: Grimer
flavorText: The wastewater coming from factories is clean these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat. They're said to be on the verge of extinction.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Muk
flavorText: Because they scatter germs everywhere, they've long been targeted for extermination, leading to a steep decline in their population.
Ability1Text: The Retreat Cost of your opponent's Poisoned Pokémon is Colorless more.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Sneasel
flavorText: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

name: Weavile
flavorText: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is heads, your opponent reveals their hand. For each heads, choose a card you find there and put it on the bottom of your opponent's deck in any order.

name: Honchkrow V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon may have up to 4 Pokémon Tools attached to it. If it loses this Ability, discard Pokémon Tools from it until only 1 remains.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.
Attack1Text: Until the end of your next turn, the Defending Pokémon's Weakness is now Darkness. (The amount of Weakness doesn't change.)
Attack2Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

name: Impidimp
flavorText: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Morgrem
flavorText: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

name: Grimmsnarl
flavorText: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Morpeko V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If you played Marnie's Pride from your hand during this turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Aggron V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Aggron VMAX
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Wormadam
flavorText: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each Pokémon in your discard pile.

name: Probopass
flavorText: It uses three small units to catch prey and battle enemies. The main body mostly just gives orders.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to the new Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Heatran
flavorText: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any Fire Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Escavalier
flavorText: They use shells they've stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They're very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 100 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

name: Klang
flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon's rotation speed increases sharply.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Klinklang
flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.
Ability1Text: Your Basic Pokémon take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Zamazenta V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 5 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Flygon V
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon VMAX, this attack does 160 more damage, and discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Gible
flavorText: Gible prefers to stay in narrow holes in the sides of caves heated by geothermal energy. This way, Gible can stay warm even during a blizzard.

name: Gabite
flavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.

name: Garchomp
flavorText: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may prevent all damage from and effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon until the end of your opponent's next turn.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Axew
flavorText: These Pokémon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other's strength.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Haxorus and put it onto this Axew to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: After battle, this Pokémon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusks—if one breaks, it will never grow back.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: Its resilient tusks are its pride and joy. It licks up dirt to take in the minerals it needs to keep its tusks in top condition.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon during their last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Dracovish V
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If you discarded a Pokémon Tool in this way, this attack does 120 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Dragon Strike.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Castform
flavorText: Its form changes depending on the weather. The rougher conditions get, the rougher Castform's disposition!
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Move a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Starly
flavorText: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Staravia
flavorText: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

name: Staraptor
flavorText: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.
Attack1Text: Your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon and all attached cards into their deck.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Bidoof
flavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

name: Bibarel
flavorText: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Arceus V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon V in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Arceus VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon V in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Minccino
flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Tornadus
flavorText: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench, you may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Drampa V
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
